# Keep documentation in sync with code

When you change **user-visible behavior**, **CLI/TUI contracts**, **data loading**, **pixi tasks**, or **project layout**, update documentation in the **same change** (do not defer).

## Required files

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `docs/DESIGN.md` | **Source of truth** for architecture and behavior. Update first. |
| `README.md` | Quick start, command examples, pixi tasks. Mirror DESIGN; keep concise. |

Also update `docs/test-data-generation.md` if `scripts/generate_test_data.py` or dataset specs change.

## When to update

Update docs if you touch any of:

- `src/main.zig`, `src/cli/**`, `src/core/**`, `src/tui/**`
- `build.zig`, `build.zig.zon`, `pixi.toml`
- `scripts/generate_test_data.py`, `scripts/capture_tui_snapshot.py`

Skip doc updates only for pure refactors with **no** behavior, CLI, TUI, or task-name changes.

## What to update in `docs/DESIGN.md`

- CLI commands, flags, limits, filter syntax
- TUI: layout, keys, mouse actions, scrolling, resize, column types, alignment
- Preview/loading APIs and threading model
- Module map if files are added/removed/renamed
- Pixi tasks and binary names
- Known limitations when constraints change
- Bump the “Last verified against” line when you materially refresh the doc

## What to update in `README.md`

- New or renamed commands / pixi tasks
- Changed defaults (paths, limits, dataset names)
- Setup/prerequisites only if they changed
- Keep the link to `docs/DESIGN.md` intact

## Checklist before finishing

- [ ] DESIGN.md describes the behavior **after** your change (not planned/future)
- [ ] README examples still run as written
- [ ] No stale references (e.g. ncurses, removed tasks, wrong dataset sizes)
- [ ] TUI keyboard/mouse table matches `src/tui/app_vaxis.zig`

## Style

- Prefer editing existing sections over adding duplicate docs
- Do not create new top-level doc files unless the user asks
- Match the tone of current DESIGN.md: factual, present tense, tables for bindings
